  "text": "Binding assay of the four stereoisomers of Brz220 to DWF4 UV-visible absorption spectroscopy provides a simple and accurate method to determine the binding of inhibitors to P450s. [CITATION_1] In the case of DWF4 expressed in E. coli, it was found that the addition of steroid ligands shifted the Soret absorption peaks of P450 from 416 nm to 383 nm.",
